<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4614.2.4>
    bibo:endPage "352" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2019-06-10" ;
    bibo:startPage "331" ;
    bibo:volume "4614" ;
    dc:creator "Davis, Hayden R.; Bauer, Aaron M.; Jackman, Todd R.; Nashriq, Izneil; Das, Indraneil" ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "Uncovering karst endemism within Borneo: two new Cyrtodactylus species from Sarawak, Malaysia" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3242446>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3242438>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3242448>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3242444>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3242450> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3242446>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Preserved type series of Cyrtodactylus limajalur sp. nov.; A) type series displaying dorsal side of body (from left to right: CAS 262849; CAS 262848; CAS 262847; and CAS 262846); and B) type series displaying ventral side of body (specimens arranged in the same order as figure 5A)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3242446/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3242438>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Preserved type series of Cyrtodactylus muluensis sp. nov. A) type series displaying dorsal side of body (from left to right: CAS 262995; CAS 262986; CAS 262983; CAS 262997; CAS 262996; and CAS 262984; CAS 262985 not shown); and B) type series displaying ventral side of body (specimens arranged in the same order as figure 1A)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3242438/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3242448>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Photograph of live paratype of Cyrtodactylus limajalur sp. nov. (CAS 262846)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3242448/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3242444>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. A) Mulu karst formation demonstrating Cyrtodactylus muluensis sp. nov. microhabitat; B) type locality of Cyrtodactylus limajalur sp. nov. The type locality of C. muluensis sp. nov. is primarily old growth with low-lying plants near the karst walls; the type locality of C. limajalur sp. nov. is on the edge of a local palm oil plantation with some old growth remaining at the base of the karst wall and on the portions of the formation at higher elevation." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3242444/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3242450>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. ML tree of Bornean Cyrtodactylus and their closely related congeners. Phylogenetic position of C. limajalur sp. nov. and C. muluensis sp. nov. is indicated by the purple and green boxes, respectively. Black circles at the node denote UF values of 95 or greater and posterior probabilities of 0.95 or greater. White circles at the node denote nodes at which either the UF or posterior probability demonstrated support, but not both." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3242450/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

